.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "December 2025" "Holberton School" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
.RI [command]

.SH DESCRIPTION
simple_shell is a simple command line interpreter that executes commands
read from the standard input.

It supports execution of commands using absolute paths and commands
found in the PATH environment variable.

The shell also implements built-in commands such as env and exit.

.SH BUILTINS
.TP
.B env
Prints the current environment variables.

.TP
.B exit
Exits the shell.

.SH USAGE
The shell works in both interactive and non-interactive modes.

.SH EXAMPLES
Interactive mode:
.PP
$ ./simple_shell
.PP
($) ls
.PP
($) env
.PP
($) exit

Non-interactive mode:
.PP
$ echo "ls" | ./simple_shell

.SH AUTHOR
Written by Yara and Manar.
